    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1371_journal_pcbi_1011814__task_001/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we used Monte Carlo CV (MCCV), with 1000 random train-test splits, using 20% of the samples in each split for evaluation. This approach allowed us to calculate not only predictive performance using standard machine learning performance metrics... Comparison of Predictive Power of SB PLS Models Compared to the MB-PLS Model Integrating All Assays... Q2 RMSE Accuracy AUC F1",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports accuracy, AUC, and F1 scores in tables. However, recall, specificity, and confusion matrix are not explicitly mentioned in the provided passages. Q2 and RMSE are reported instead of recall/specificity.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c01327",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Model performance metrics table: accuracy, recall, specificity, F1-score, AUC, confusion matrix for test set predictions",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:33:03.161753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1371_journal_pcbi_1011814__task_001/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We used multiblock variable importance in projection (MB-VIP) to estimate feature importance and coupled it with permutation testing to obtain empirical p-values... Statistically Significant Variable Comparison between Univariate Statistics and MB-PLS Models",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses MB-VIP and empirical p-values via permutation testing. However, the specific p<0.01 threshold is not universally applied; paper states 'The optimal significance level for p-values was \u03b1 = 0.05 for experiment 2, \u03b1 = 0.01 for experiment 4, and the Bonferroni correction for experiments 1 and 3'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c01327",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Feature importance table with MB-VIP scores and empirical p-values for all features, sorted by statistical significance (p<0.01 threshold)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:33:03.161753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1371_journal_pcbi_1011814__task_001/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We estimated the number of LVs using a grid search combined with k-fold cross-validation (CV)... Another advantage of the MB-PLS model is that the model helps to identify which assays contribute most... The bar chart shows how much of the explained variance for each latent variable (LV) in the model comes from each data block.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes grid search for LV estimation and shows block importance by LV in figures, but does not explicitly describe an 'AUC versus number of components' plot. The paper uses Q2, RMSE, accuracy, AUC, and F1 as performance metrics but the specific visualization of AUC vs. LV count is not detailed in passages.",
