    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/hierarchical-clustering-dendrogram-interpretation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The statistically significant MB-PLS features were clustered based on their intensity correlations. We computed a dissimilarity matrix D (M \u00d7 M) where dij=|1\u2212rij| where r ij is the correlation coefficient between the i th and j th feature. We then applied agglomerative hierarchical clustering using the farthest point (complete) linkage and selected the optimal number of clusters by the highest mean silhouette score.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the clustering procedure but does not explicitly name or reference a method called 'MamsiStructSearch.get_correlation_clusters()'. The paper describes the underlying algorithm (hierarchical clustering with silhouette optimization) but the specific function name is not confirmed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c01327",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
