    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-feature-annotation-aggregation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To investigate whether the MB-PLS derived correlation clusters are structurally related, we used retention time (RT) matching and mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) differences to find possible isotopologues and adducts both within and across the assays... Additionally, our structural search tool can use region of interest (ROI) files from peakPantheR software, enabling automated annotation",
