    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolite-structural-annotation-integration/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To investigate whether the MB-PLS derived correlation clusters are structurally related, we used retention time (RT) matching and mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) differences to find possible isotopologues and adducts both within and across the assays. We call these structurally linked features structural groups... Additionally, our structural search tool can use region of interest (ROI) files from peakPantheR software, enabling automated annotation (minimum level 3) of features based on m/z and RT for a given chromatography.",
      "asbval:note": "Core workflow is explicitly described in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c01327",
