      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-feature-selection-significance-filtering/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MB-PLS model can narrow the list of significant predictors by around 90% in comparison to univariate methods. This allows for an easier interpretation of the results... The statistically significant MB-PLS features were clustered based on their intensity correlations... we used retention time (RT) matching and mass-to-charge ratio (m/z) differences to find possible isotopologues and adducts both within and across the assays.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates feature filtering reduces noise and enables downstream structural annotation (isotopologues, adducts, cross-assay links).",
