      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The LC-MS data used in this study were preprocessed and presented in the form of feature abundance tables... These data were converted to mzML format using ProteoWizard, preprocessed using XCMS and nPYc toolbox software resulting in 681, 4886, and 2091 features for HILIC+, lipid RPC+, and lipid RPC\u2013 respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates that assay identity (HILIC+, lipid RPC+, lipid RPC\u2013) is preserved and samples are aligned across assays. The workflow maintains sample correspondence across blocks.",
